}","s":"Env","u":"/docs/Template Engine/appendix","h":"#env","p":3},{"i":14,"t":"Template Engine Privacy Policy","s":"Privacy Policy","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"","p":13},{"i":16,"t":"The Template Engine does not collect or transmit any personal data outside your organization’s environment. All data processed by the Template Engine remains within your Dataverse and Power Platform infrastructure.","s":"1. Data Collection","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"#1-data-collection","p":13},{"i":18,"t":"The Template Engine processes data as defined by your templates, triggers, and user actions. No data is shared with third parties by the Template Engine itself.","s":"2. Data Usage","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"#2-data-usage","p":13},{"i":20,"t":"Data security is managed by your organization’s Power Platform and Dataverse security policies. Access to the Template Engine and its configuration should be restricted to authorized users.","s":"3. Data Security","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"#3-data-security","p":13},{"i":22,"t":"Users are responsible for ensuring that templates and triggers do not expose or misuse sensitive information. Always follow your organization’s data protection and privacy guidelines when configuring and using the Template Engine.","s":"4. User Responsibility","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"#4-user-responsibility","p":13},{"i":24,"t":"This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time. Continued use of the Template Engine constitutes acceptance of the latest policy. If you have questions or concerns about privacy, please contact your system administrator or data protection officer.","s":"5. Changes to This Policy","u":"/docs/Template Engine/privacy-policy","h":"#5-changes-to-this-policy","p":13},{"i":26,"t":"Template Engine Terms and Conditions","s":"Terms and Conditions","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"","p":25},{"i":28,"t":"The Template Engine is provided for automating record operations within Microsoft Power Platform environments. You are responsible for ensuring that all templates, triggers, and actions comply with your organization’s data policies and security requirements.","s":"1. Usage","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#1-usage","p":25},{"i":30,"t":"The Template Engine processes and modifies data in Dataverse tables as defined by your templates and triggers. It is your responsibility to validate templates before deployment to avoid unintended data changes or loss. Always test templates in a non-production environment before applying them to live data.","s":"2. Data Integrity","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#2-data-integrity","p":25},{"i":32,"t":"Do not include sensitive or confidential information in templates, triggers, or environment variables unless proper security measures are in place. Access to the Template Engine and its configuration should be restricted to authorized users only.","s":"3. Security","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#3-security","p":25},{"i":34,"t":"The authors and contributors of the Template Engine are not liable for any data loss, corruption, or security breaches resulting from its use. Use of the Template Engine is at your own risk.","s":"4. Liability","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#4-liability","p":25},{"i":36,"t":"The Template Engine is provided as-is, without any guarantee of support or future updates. Contributions and suggestions are welcome via the project’s repository.","s":"5. Support and Updates","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#5-support-and-updates","p":25},{"i":38,"t":"These terms and conditions may be updated at any time. Continued use of the Template Engine constitutes acceptance of the latest terms. If you do not agree to these terms, do not use the Template Engine.","s":"6. Changes to Terms","u":"/docs/Template Engine/terms-and-conditions","h":"#6-changes-to-terms","p":25},{"i":40,"t":"Template Engine Help","s":"Help","u":"/docs/Template Engine/help","h":"","p":39},{"i":42,"t":"Review the Introduction to understand the core concepts. See the Terms and Conditions before using the Template Engine.","s":"Getting Started","u":"/docs/Template Engine/help","h":"#getting-started","p":39},{"i":44,"t":"Creating a Template Group: Define a group of template items to automate actions on Dataverse records. Use filtering expressions to control when groups run. Defining Template Items: Use the Monaco Editor for intelligent suggestions. Reference source, env, and faker in your expressions. Setting Up Triggers: Configure triggers to run templates on specific events (e.g., record updates). Monitoring Jobs: Check the Template Jobs log for history and troubleshooting.","s":"Common Tasks","u":"/docs/Template Engine/help","h":"#common-tasks","p":39},{"i":46,"t":"Templates not running? Ensure triggers are correctly configured and enabled. Check filtering expressions for syntax errors. Unexpected data changes? Test templates in a non-production environment first. Review template logic and conditions. Editor issues? Refresh the page if Monaco Editor suggestions do not appear. Ensure your browser supports modern JavaScript features.","s":"Troubleshooting","u":"/docs/Template Engine/help","h":"#troubleshooting","p":39},{"i":48,"t":"Q: How do I reference fields from the source record? A: Use source.fieldname in your template expressions. Q: Can I use environment variables? A: Yes, use env.variablename in your templates. Q: How do I roll back changes? A: Use the Roll Back feature in the Template Jobs log to delete records created by a job.","s":"FAQ","u":"/docs/Template Engine/help","h":"#faq","p":39},{"i":50,"t":"Template Engine Introduction","s":"Introduction","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"","p":49},{"i":52,"t":"A group of template items. Defines the scope of actions and the source type. A group can be filtered by a filtering expression.","s":"Template Group","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#template-group","p":49},{"i":54,"t":"Runs only if the source state is Active statecode != 1","s":"Conditional Template Group Filtering","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#conditional-template-group-filtering","p":49},{"i":56,"t":"The target table object definition in JSON. { \"leadid\": \"{{ source.leadid }}\", \"new_expirydate\": \"{{ !source.address1_line1? (source.new_expirydate ?? date.now | date.add_years 2) : (source.new_expirydate ?? date.now | date.add_years 1) }}\", \"leadqualitycode\": \"{{ !source.address1_line1? 1 : 3}}\"}","s":"Template Item","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#template-item","p":49},{"i":58,"t":"Using \"template:condition\" property. Runs only if the source owning business unit has country code and source has an auto number. \"template:condition\": \"{{ source.owningbusinessunit.xrm_countrycode && source.xrm_autonumber}}\"","s":"Conditional Template Item Filtering","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#conditional-template-item-filtering","p":49},{"i":60,"t":"Table represents plugin processing steps. Each record represents an SDK step. On save, a relationship is created for the polymorphic lookup on the json, if it does not exist, 1:N target record type specified in the trigger record.","s":"Template Triggers","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#template-triggers","p":49},{"i":62,"t":"Log of triggered groups. Every time an event is triggered by the template trigger definitions. A job is created for history. A job will run a group of items using a plugin step defined in the trigger table or will be executed by a Power Automate flow \" [TemplateEngine] Apply Template Job\"","s":"Template Jobs","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#template-jobs","p":49},{"i":64,"t":"Template job is automatically related to the target record initated the job. Therefore you can find all related job runs to a specific record.","s":"Source Popolymorphic Lookup","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#source-popolymorphic-lookup","p":49},{"i":66,"t":"The editor uses the Monaco Editor, providing intelligent suggestions and auto-completions for template expressions. As you type, the editor offers context-aware completions for properties like source, env, and faker, making it easy to construct dynamic expressions. For example, typing source. will suggest available fields from the source record, while env. provides environment variables, and faker. exposes bogus fake data generation for testing. The schema functionality powers these suggestions, ensuring that only valid properties in all entities metadata and methods are shown based on your template item entity context.","s":"Monaco Editor for Template Items","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#monaco-editor-for-template-items","p":49},{"i":69,"t":"{ \"url\": \"{{env.xrm_EnvironmentUrl}}\"}","s":"Environment Variables","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"","p":49},{"i":71,"t":"{ \"xrm_countrycode\": \"{{source.owningbusinessunit.xrm_countrycode}}\"}","s":"Navigation Properties","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#navigation-properties","p":49},{"i":73,"t":"Bogus { \"emailaddress1\": \"{{faker.internet.email()}}\"}","s":"Testing","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#testing","p":49},{"i":75,"t":"On a job. Click \"Roll Back\" to delete records created by the job. That is useful for testing.","s":"Rollback","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#rollback","p":49},{"i":77,"t":"Charles Llamas for Code Editor PCF component","s":"Credits","u":"/docs/Template Engine/intro","h":"#credits","p":49}],"index":{"version":"2.3.9","fields":["t"],"fieldVectors":[["t/2",[0,3.883]],["t/4",[1,0.489,2,1.173,3,4.891]],["t/6",[1,0.471,4,2.363,5,2.971,6,2.809,7,1.603,8,1.41,9,1.854,10,2.809,11,1.854,12,0.899,13,2.073,14,2.809,15,2.809,16,1.535,17,2.073,18,1.205,19,2.809,20,2.809]],["t/8",[1,0.441,5,2.36,8,2.215,16,2.41,21,2.912,22,3.198,23,3.198,24,3.02,25,3.198,26,2.692,27,3.198,28,1.482]],["t/10